He's heading for a giant strike.
On Friday, the League of Trade Unions and the National Union of Workers’ Councils (MOSZ) will form their strike committee to coordinate Monday’s unlimited strike.
A protest public meeting is taking place on Saturday, and on Monday - the day of the final vote on the health insurance law - work will be stopped.
The event will surely cause a serious disruption of transport, as railway transport will almost completely stop and within 13 hours employees of the Budapest Transport Company (BKV) will also be on strike.
On Friday afternoon, the League Association will share with the National Union of Workers’ Councils the details of the jointly organised Monday strike.
The strike commission LIGA - MOSZ will also be formed, which will coordinate Monday's event.
A public protest rally is taking place on Saturday, and from Monday, unions joining the strike will stop work indefinitely unless an agreement is reached with the government.
This means that no deadline has been set for ending the strike, which will begin on the day of the parliamentary vote on the Health Insurance Act.
If Parliament fails to pass the health insurance law, the unions will immediately withdraw the call for a strike.
However, if the legislation is voted on, the strike committees will meet and decide on the next procedure.
According to the agenda of the Parliament's meeting on Monday, it is also possible that the law on health insurance will be voted on only in the late evening, or at night.
Due to the start of the strike on Monday, it is possible to expect serious traffic disruptions: work on the railway will be stopped indefinitely, part of Budapest's public transport and more than half of the Volan companies can stop in the morning.
At the same time, half of the lane will be closed in many parts of the country.
Numerous trade unions and civil society organisations have joined the call for strikes, the list of which is constantly updated on the League’s website.
Some organizations have announced a strike indefinitely, others have announced a temporary cessation of work.
Until Thursday afternoon, the Hungarian State Railways (MAV) and the Independent Union of Railway Workers (VDSZSZ) could not agree on sufficient services, while more and more people travel on the railway at the beginning of the Christmas holidays.
According to the current announcements, the strike will be held at BKV from the beginning of operation until 1 pm, from 7 am to 9 am at Budapest Airport, a four-hour strike will be organized by the Trade Unions of Workers in the Energy Industry LIGA, to the 2-, respectively 2-8-hour stoppage of work by the Trade Union of Teachers and Democrats.
The Union of Hungarian Physicians will strike alternately across the country, the Democratic Union of Health and Social Workers (EDDSZ), part of the Cooperation Forum of Trade Unions (SZEF), is holding a two-hour warning strike.
The most important of the four demands formulated by League associations is for the government to withdraw the health insurance reform proposal and submit a new concept for public discussion.
The second requirement is that the new method of calculating pensions, valid from next year, be introduced gradually.
Thirdly, the possibility of early retirement for the sectors concerned to be included in the scheme before 2010 should be ensured.
The fourth reason for the event is that the Independent Union of Railway Workers (VDSZSZ), which falls under the League trade union association, does not accept the offer of the Ministry of Economy and Transport regarding railway branches, and expects another offer.
