Holidays are not free everywhere
In Hungary, holidays are precisely stipulated by law and it has already become common practice to move working days around the holidays, which is expected to happen less often in the next year.
In the European Union and in America, holidays are not unified.
The Hungarian legal system distinguishes between national and state holidays and days of rest.
The days of work rest are usually associated with church holidays or important historical events.
We also celebrate the New Year: the last day of the old and the first day of the new year is a work holiday - for the New Year already so that people can rest after New Year.
During the year we have a total of eleven free holidays.
The national holiday is March 15th to celebrate the Revolution of 1848 and October 23rd, the commemorative day of the Revolution of 1956.
On August 20th we celebrate the founding of the state, on May 1st the work, on November 1st and 2nd we remember the deceased relatives and friends.
In addition, there are two-day holidays of Easter, Summer and Christmas.
Since our national, national, or religious holidays rarely fall on weekends according to the calendar, it has become a practice to move the working day in cases where we would only work one day before or after the holiday.
However, the price for the extended weekend is that the previous Saturdays we stay in the workplace and in the school.
The day which immediately precedes or follows the holiday is worked out by the Minister of Labour in a special decree for many years.
The legislation applies equally to all employers and workers employed by them, to public servants and to persons in the public service.
However, it does not apply to companies and institutions that are in operation without interruption or with regard to their destination, even on days of working rest.
This year, the work order will change only around the end of the year: from December 24, life in the country will almost stop, because according to the experience so far, most people "work" the days between Christmas and New Year in advance or thus take advantage of the saved holiday.
Next year, a few of our holidays fall into the middle, respectively, at the end of the week, so there will be less workday shifts than this year.
For the first time, the calendar changes around the holiday so that the workers can then stay at home for four days of taste.
Saturday 26th of April will be a working day, so that Friday 2nd of May can be a day of rest.
Another move is related to the holiday of October 23rd: on Saturday, October 18th, work will be done instead of Friday, October 24th.
At the end of the year, however, next year will be able to take place completely in the name of holidays, because from December 24 they will have a non-stop holiday almost everywhere, even though New Year's Eve falls on Wednesday.
