Congress approves MiFID transposition effective November 1
At the same time as parliamentary negotiations ended today with a vote by Congress on the novelties included by the Senate in the bill, the government submitted a public hearing of a regulation developing the new law with the aim of both coming into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of each party unanimously highlighted the efforts of MEPs and Senators to negotiate and agree on the best standard to ensure the protection of investors and the detailed regulation of the activities of entities necessary for the effective functioning of markets.
The MiFID Directive, which regulates the Securities Trading Act, envisages the modernisation of financial markets while strengthening investor protection, improves the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and promotes cooperation between the various supervisory authorities of the European Union.
This new regulation will enable the provision of financial advisory services to both specialised companies and natural or legal persons and creates a new type of financial services company (ESIS), financial advisory company (AFI), which joins securities companies, securities brokerage firms, and securities companies.
In addition, the number of systems for the execution of transactions with financial instruments is expanded by joining multilateral trading systems and order internalisation systems to the regulated secondary markets, which will compete with current stockbrokers.
The law also obliges investment firms to disseminate information on key aspects of their business profile, risk exposure and risk management on the market, and requires CNMV to keep a record of all operations performed to simplify supervision.
During the debate in the Congressional Trade Commission, a number of adjustments were included, among which stands out the fact that securitised claims were considered a "complex" financial instrument due to the high risk to the investor that was demonstrated by what happened in the US with high-risk (hypothesized) loans.
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally designate the functions that bachelors in economics and business management can hold 30 years after the Royal Decree, which sets out the professional functions reserved for economists, was approved in 1977.
The Senate also included the creation of new professions in the financial sector, such as an intermediary that will work externally, will not require permission from CNMV and will be able to provide product trading and client acquisition services for various investment firms at the same time.
Harmonized ISC increased by five decimal places to 4.1% in November
This indicator, which is later used by Eurostat to calculate the inflation index of the European Union, provides preliminary information on how prices developed in Spain during the month of November.
Its publication is consistent with the policies of Eurostat and the European Central Bank (ECB) to provide data in time and quality comparable to those achieved in the United States.
This preliminary indicator is calculated using the same process as that used for the Harmonised Index of Consumer Prices, but using different statistical modelling methods to estimate information that is not yet available at the time of publication.
The Spanish INE (State Institute for Statistics) recalled that the information provided by this preliminary indicator is only indicative and therefore does not necessarily coincide with the final data, which will be available on 14 December of this year.
"The ISC will continue to remain at a relatively high level"
