In any case, Solbes stated in the Congressional bulletins that "although it will not be a favorable number", Spain's inflation differential to the monetary union has remained "more or less" the same over the past two years.
He also explained that November "was less surprising" than the previous month, when the government did not count on such a high increase.
"We expected a value of around 4%," the economy minister said of the data presented today.
