What kind of insurance is suitable for me?
Car insurance that protects the driver in the event of an accident. represents a significant expense, which depends on various factors such as age, condition, sex, length of hold of the driver's license, the type of vehicle to be insured or its use, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing the right car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to be clear about what we are talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurer and the insurer.
This commitment takes the form of an insurance contract, which provides that the insurance company will receive an agreed insurance amount in a certain amount to take care of paying damages in the event of an insurance event.
Insurance is the price of insurance, which is determined with regard to various factors such as age, condition, sex, length of holding a driver’s license, type of vehicle being insured or its use, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices based on statistics, so the higher the probability of an accident, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both people over the age of 25 and women have to pay lower insurance, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, on the basis of checks, insurance companies concluded that people living in marriage have fewer accidents than single drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of rides, and thus the probability of having an accident.
Increasing the frequency of rides increases the likelihood.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when determining the price of insurance.
Therefore, the driver must study the situation well in order to choose the insurance that best suits his profile of the insurer.
Here we will show you the most important variables for choosing a type of insurance, which, in addition to satisfying the type of insurer, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of twenty-five face a variety of disadvantages, such as little driving experience and short driving licenses when they want to take out insurance at an affordable price.
Although insurance against all risks is ideal for good coverage, there are also cheaper options.
The most careful drivers can choose insurance against all risks with an insurance discount so that they get insurance cover for all risks, but at a more affordable price.
This type of contract would entail the participation of the client in the payment of the insurance event.
"The part of the insurance event payment provided by the client will be determined in advance when determining the insurance price, which will be the higher the lower the participation would be," explains Luis Noguera, Chief Executive Officer of First Europe in Spain, an online insurance broker.
Another option is insurance extended to other road users by insuring the customer against damage caused to other people, but not against damage to his own car.
In addition, he would be insured against theft, fire and loss of a vehicle.
Recommendations.
If you are under twenty-five, try to be attentive and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce your insurance in the future.
The bonus is a reduction in the basic rate that an insurance company has.
On the contrary, the malus is an increase in the mentioned basic rate.
"Bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company has had a good year, it will be able to afford to increase the bonus," explains Noguera.
After exceeding the twenty-five year limit, it is easier for drivers to get insurance, as the client’s risk index is reduced, thanks to the experience gained.
For this reason, it is most recommended to arrange insurance against all risks with a discount.
"Young people usually cannot take advantage of the experience gained in advance at the time of the accident, or even during the driving," the director of the European company in Spain assures, adding that most of the accidents occur in the second year of the procedure, when the "fear of the newcomer" has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but does not yet have children, it is better to arrange insurance against all risks, if his economic situation allows it.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies as clients with the lowest risk index and therefore their surcharges will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with an insurance discount (which could be 300 euros) or with a high bonus, insurance extended to other road users, starting with the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
"Their driving is calmer and their purchasing power is higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount," Luis Noguera said.
Pensioners are advised to take out insurance against all risks with an insurance discount (which is <0xE2><0x82><0xAC>150) or insurance extended to other participants of the operation, if a high bonus has been achieved.
It must be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects the driver in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a significant expense, which is a good reason to properly study the insurance options that would suit us most in view of our personal situation.
